{CHARACTER_NAME}: Lock, Stock & Two Smoking Barrels
{META_DATA}: By Guy Ritchie
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. INTERROGATION ROOM - PRESENT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This whole scene is shot using only extreme close-ups of eyes, cards, tapping fingers and mouths.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We open on a bright pair of eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One is bruised and slightly swollen, but this does not detract from their clarity.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EDDY
{DIALOGUE}: Three card brag is a simple form of poker; you are dealt only three cards and these you can't change.
{DIALOGUE}: If you don't look at your cards you're a `blind man' and you only put in half the stake.
{DIALOGUE}: Three of any kind is the highest you can get: the odds are four hundred and twenty- five to one.
{DIALOGUE}: Then it's a running flush - you know, all the same suit running in order; then a straight, then a flush, then a pair, and finally whatever the highest card you are holding.
{DIALOGUE}: There are some tell- tale signs that are valuable; I am not going to tell you them because it took me long enough to learn them, but these can only help a player, not make one.
{DIALOGUE}: So you want to play?
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO BLACK. THE FIRST OF THE CREDITS APPEAR ON THE SCREEN.
{META_DATA}: FADE IN:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: What have you got?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We cut to a beady pair of eyes and then to his cards as they are turned over: three hearts of no consecutive numbers are exposed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: That's a good hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A flush beats my pair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: What about you?
{META_DATA}: Cut from completed film.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another pair of excited eyes widen to the question.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see more cards: a run is revealed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And here's me trying to explain the game to you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hustlers, you're all hustlers!
