{DIALOGUE}: Take a bag, take a bag.
{DIALOGUE}: I took a bag, I took a bag home last night and she cost a lot more than ten pounds I can tell ya.
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me if I am going too cheap.
{DIALOGUE}: Not ninety, not eighty, not forty, half that and half that again, that's right, ten pounds.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't think 'cos it's sealed up it's an empty box.
{DIALOGUE}: The only man who sells empty boxes is the undertaker, and by the look of some of you here today I would make more money with me measuring tape.
