{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HATCHER (interrupts j I know you're not in, which means nobody cares what you know.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two hundred and fifty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hatchet and EDDY minutely study each other's hairlines, waiting for a nervous droplet to appear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sweat breaks; a drop on Ed's forehead, fills frame.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slowly we follow a droplet's journey coursing down Eddy's brow Eventually this is met by a large unblinking eye, at this point the pause is broken.
