{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This next section is subtitled.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is to keep everyone, even those familiar with cockney rhyming slang up to speed with the narration, of which even Tom is unsure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As with the police scene earlier this is a voice-over and we cut to the relevant scenes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARFLYJACK
{META_DATA}: (voice-over)
{DIALOGUE}: Rory's got few interests in life; darky music, football, bees and honey and kicking the shit out of anyone that interferes with that shortlist.
{DIALOGUE}: A few nights ago Rory's Roger iron rusted, so he has gone to the battle-cruiser to watch the end of a football game.
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody is watching the custard so he has turned the channel over.
{DIALOGUE}: A fat man's north opens and he wanders up and turns the Liza over.
{DIALOGUE}: `Now fuck off and watch it somewhere else.'
{DIALOGUE}: Rory knows claret is imminent, but he doesn't want to miss the end of the game; so, calm as a coma, he stands and picks up a fire extinguisher and he walks straight past the jam rolls who are ready for action, then he plonks it outside the entrance.
{DIALOGUE}: He then orders an Aristotle of the most ping pong oddly in the nuclear sub and switches back to his footer.
{DIALOGUE}: `That's fucking it,' says the man.
{DIALOGUE}: Rory gobs out a mouthful of booze covering fatty; he flicks a flaming match into his bird's nest and the man lit up like a leaking gas pipe.
{DIALOGUE}: Rory, unfazed, turned back to watch his game.
