{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ed opens the bag.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EDDY
{DIALOGUE}: There's nothing in it!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SOAP
{DIALOGUE}: What do you mean?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EDDY
{DIALOGUE}: I mean it's fucking empty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BACON lunges forward and stares in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sticks his hand in and extracts an A4 envelope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They look puzzled.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ed feels the package and starts to tear the top off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As this is done it creates a split screen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the other side of the picture, Tom is on a London bridge with the car boot open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at the guns with regret and give them one last polish.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he folds the guns up and places them on top of a handrail.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Simultaneously Ed extracts a Sotherby's brochure on shotguns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They still look confused.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They turn the brochure upside down and recognize the shotguns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slowly they start to turn the pages.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Torn pushes the shotguns over the top rail: they fall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He starts walking but stops for some reason.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He retreads his steps and peers over; the guns had just fallen on to a shelf.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ed sees the price of the guns: a series of alarming zooms cut between eyes and prices.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They panic and reach for their mobile phones.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tom is climbing over the bridge now and has to hold on to the rail with one arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ed starts screaming at the other two that the number is engaged and asks them to put their phones down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tom now had one hand on the guns and one on the rail.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His mobile phone starts to ring in his top pocket; he has either to drop the guns or let go of the rail to answer the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shot freezes.
